column1: #Text=The Miami Heat defeated the Toronto Raptors , 104 - 89 , at American Airlines Arena on Saturday afternoon .
#Text=The Heat ( 32 - 34 ) checked in to Wednesday 000s contest with only seven wins in their previous seven games , but the Heat ( 38 - 28 ) were able to prevail with a much - needed win .

#Text=The Heat ( 38 - 28 ) were able to outperform Toronto ( 38 - 28 ) to a 38 percent success rate from the field , and 13 percent from three - point range , while also holding the Raptors to a 38 percent success rate from behind the arc .
#Text=The Raptors were led by DeMar DeRozan 000s 17 points , which he supplemented with four rebounds , two assists and one steal .
#Text=Serge Ibaka was next with nine points , four rebounds , an assist and three blocks .

column1: #Text=Jonas Valanciunas posted a 10 - point , 10 - rebound double - double that also included an assist .
#Text=Fred VanVleet supplied five points , four rebounds , one assist and a steal .
#Text=Tyler Johnson paced the bench with 16 points , three rebounds , three assists and a steal .
#Text=Hassan Whiteside posted a 12 - point , 14 - rebound double - double that also included an assist , four blocks and a steal .

#Text=Goran Dragic and Dion Waiters supplied matching 15 - point efforts , with the former also supplying a pair of assists and a steal , and the latter supplying five assists , one rebound and one steal .
